Package com.github.yeetmanlord.zeta_core.sql.impl

Class AbstractSQLDataStorer<PrimaryKeyType>

java.lang.Object
com.github.yeetmanlord.zeta_core.data.DataStorer
com.github.yeetmanlord.zeta_core.sql.impl.AbstractSQLDataStorer<PrimaryKeyType>
Type Parameters:
PrimaryKeyType - The type of the primary key of the table.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISQLTableHandler<PrimaryKeyType>
public abstract class AbstractSQLDataStorer<PrimaryKeyType> extends DataStorer implements ISQLTableHandler<PrimaryKeyType>
This is an implementation of ISQLTableHandler. This is used for data storers that store data in one table in a database. It can also have a related table that stores related data. For example, say you have a file called player-info.yml. In it, you have a list of UUIDs and their balance. Within that file, you may also have a few additional config options. You could specify something like a max balance, and a default balance. These are not related to the player's balance so would be stored in a related table. You could also just separate that into a different file if you so choose.

Additionally, this class has a connected ISQL object. This is used to quickly load and save data to the database. If you just want to store data in a table, you can use AbstractUntypedSQLDataStorer

Author:
YeetManLord
